title: The Collected Buffy S9 (Dark Horse|2011-13|Digital-1280|Empire)
description:
Contains: Everything published under the "Season Nine" banner, as far as I'm aware.

BUFFY: SEASON NINE - Issues 1 thru 25, compiled per narrative continuity from Empire's Digital Lo-Res original releases (issues ~9 thru 25) or re-releases (issues 1 thru ~8). With variant covers for issues 1 thru 7 courtesy of Minutemen-DTs.

MAGICAL MYSTERY TOUR - "Season Nine" prequel short, starring Spike, by TheGroup.

IN SPACE NO ONE CAN HEAR YOU SLAY - 2012 FCBD short, with a Xenomorph cameo. Sort of.

LOVE VERSUS LIFE - 2013 sidequel issue, serialized in "DH Presents". Digital Hi-Res.

ANGEL & FAITH - 1 thru 25, details as for "Buffy", Minutemen variants up to issue 9.

SPIKE: A DARK PLACE - Five-issue mini-series, compiled into one. Digital Lo-Res.

WILLOW: WONDERLAND - The second five-issue mini-series, also compiled into one. Digital Lo-Res releases by Empire, and featuring the full set of exquisite variant covers, provided by Tarutaru-Novus.

Misses: The third five-issue mini-series, starring Drusilla. This was originally supposed to have been published in mid-2012, spinning out of the "Angel & Faith" arc "Daddy Issues", in which the character makes an appearance, but has yet to see the light of day. For more details, see e.g. <a href=" http://www.comicbookresources.com/?page=article&id=37271" rel="nofollow" target="_NEW"> http://www.comicbookresources.com/?page=article&id=37271</a>  and a number of follow-up articles accessible from there.
